(114420, 'When the Darkness comes', 2019, 'Taking around an hour on the first play-through, "When The Darkness Comes" feels like you’re wandering around a glitchy hard drive full of abstract dreams and beautiful nightmares. The narrator initially makes it feel like a comedic game, but it soon starts to take a darker tone as you travel down the bizarre broken rabbit hole that explores the darkest themes of the human mind.', 'https://images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_cover_big/co1ivq.jpg', 17637),

